dct_title_s: HEDENDAAGSCHE HISTORIE, of TEGENWOORDIGE STAAT VAN ALLE VOLKEREN; VII. Deel
dct_description_sm: Polar projection with California as an unlabeled island on an unrolled sheet nailed above a doorway on the top section of a title page. Title page shows the workings of the beaver trade with trappers and traders exchanging goods for pelts. J.C. Philips inv. et fecit 1735. (lower left).
